## Summary
- Add `bit hq` command for ghq-compatible repository management
- Change clone shorthand syntax: remove `@` prefix, use `:` for subdir

## Changes

### bit hq (ghq-compatible)
- `bit hq get user/repo` ’ clone to `~/bhq/user/repo`
- `bit hq get gitlab.com/user/repo` ’ clone to `~/bhq/gitlab.com/user/repo`
- `bit hq get user/repo:src/lib` ’ sparse checkout
- `bit hq list` ’ list cloned repos
- `bit hq root` ’ show root directory
- `BHQ_ROOT` env to override root

### Clone shorthand syntax
- `bit clone user/repo` ’ GitHub clone (no `@` prefix)
- `bit clone user/repo:src/lib` ’ sparse checkout with `:` separator
- `bit clone gitlab.com/user/repo` ’ other hosts
- Ambiguity check: error if local directory conflicts

